Singleton design pattern:

1. The singleton pattern is a design pattern that restricts the instantiation of a class to one object.
2. Java Singleton Pattern is one of the Gangs of Four Design patterns and comes in the Creational Design Pattern category. 
3. Singleton pattern restricts the instantiation of a class and ensures that only one instance of the class exists 
   in the java virtual machine.
4. The singleton class must provide a global access point to get the instance of the class.
5. Singleton pattern is used for logging, drivers objects, caching and thread pool.
6. Singleton design pattern is also used in other design patterns like Abstract Factory, Builder, Prototype, Facade etc.
7. Singleton design pattern is used in core java classes also, for example java.lang.Runtime, java.awt.Desktop.

References: https://www.journaldev.com/1377/java-singleton-design-pattern-best-practices-examples
